Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_metric_table_heading(25.10)          create_metric_table_heading(25.10)

Name
       create_metric_table_heading - Create a new metric heading

Syntax
       create_metric_table_heading

       [-help]

       [-format {html excel text}]

       [-id <heading_id>]

       -page <page_name>

       -title <heading_title>[-type {fixed collapse}]< >

       Create a new metric heading.

       You  create  the heading for the metric page you created using the cre-
       ate_metric_page. After specifying the metric table heading, you  create
       the metric table using the create_metric_table command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man create_metric_table_heading

       -format {html excel text}
              Specifies configuration for the report_metric format.

              Date_type: enum, optional

       -id <heading_id>
              Specifies the id for the new heading.

              Date_type: string, optional

       -page <page_name>
              Specifies the page name where the heading will be added.

              Date_type: string, required

       -title <heading_title>
              Specifies the title of the heading.

              Date_type: string, required

       -type {fixed collapse}
              Specifies the type of heading element, fixed or collapse.

              Date_type: enum, optional

Example
       The  following commands create  the table_s metric table with the head-
       ing Average Timing Values Per Snapshot:

       innovus2> create_metric_table_heading -id statistics -page User \

         -title "Average Timing Values Per Snapshot"

       innovus3> create_metric_table  -id table_s -heading statistics \

         -per_snapshot -type  horizontal

Related Information
